transport: institutionalize the data-sync layer

Names the bounded data-sync institution: catch-up byte movement,
rebuild byte movement, barrier exchange, achieved-frontier report,
and the lineage gate that fails closed on stale or overlapping
traffic. The institution does not own recovery classification,
session lifecycle policy, failover decisions, or operator
publication — those belong to later phases.

Splits transport into per-responsibility files so the boundaries
are visible on the page:

  executor.go         — session lifecycle + probe (observation only)
  catchup_sender.go   — primary-side catch-up byte movement
  rebuild_sender.go   — primary-side rebuild byte movement
  barrier.go          — typed BarrierResponse and helpers
  replica.go          — per-message-type handlers, lineage gate

Catch-up and rebuild each keep their own ship loop. The two
protocols look similar today but have different terminators (barrier
vs RebuildDone) and shouldn't share a hidden implementation that
would mask their divergence later.

BarrierResponse replaces the bare 8-byte uint64 wire reply with a
typed struct {AchievedLSN uint64}. The replica reports what Sync()
actually returned; the primary returns that value verbatim. Short
or unexpected payloads now fail closed instead of silently
fabricating a frontier.

Replica handler dispatch extracted into named per-message methods
(handleShipEntry, handleProbeReq, handleRebuildBlock,
handleRebuildDone, handleBarrierReq), each fronted by the same
acceptMutationLineage gate.

Five new fail-closed tests prove the institution's negative space:

  - overlapping sessions: higher lineage bumps active state, older
    session's in-flight frames are rejected
  - primary mid-rebuild crash: subsequent higher-lineage session
    converges, achieved frontier reflects the new session
  - replica disconnects before BarrierResp: primary surfaces failure
    with no fabricated AchievedLSN
  - stale Ship after newer Rebuild: cross-message-type lineage
    rejection
  - probe during rebuild: probe is observation, does not disturb
    activeLineage

Plus a typed-barrier roundtrip + short-payload-fails-closed test.

docs/data-sync-institution.md names what this layer owns, what it
does not, and the explicit carry-forward to later phases.
